 Soccer Football – La Liga Santander – Real Madrid v Leganes – Santiago Bernabeu, Madrid, Spain – October 30, 2019  Real Madrid’s Federico Valverde reacts  REUTERS/Susana Vera  Midfielder Valverde was sent off in the closing stages of extra time in Sunday’s final against local rivals Atletico Madrid when the 21-year-old chopped down Spain striker Alvaro Morata as he charged through on goal. Real won 4-1 on penalties after the match finished goalless, and Atletico coach Diego Simeone said that Valverde’s foul “was the most important moment of the match”. The suspension means that Uruguayan Valverde will miss Real’s home match against Sevilla on Saturday. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .